As with the anti-locking of ABS brakes and will pass with the ESP stability control, emergency braking support systems will have to be a mandatory element in European cars.
In fact, they are already in all tourism and light commercial vehicles of new registration, while for the rest a period of deficiency is fixed until the end of February 2011.
The aim of the measure, imposed by the European Union, is to increase the protection of pedestrians, although, in its way of working, it can also help prevent many collisions by scope.
The emergency brake assistant does what it does is to increase the pressure on the brakes in case of an emergency, which the system detects by the driver's piston.
